benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/catalog/phase - Retrieve phase for a given subscription and date

covered: Valid request / primary success path: TC01 verifies 200 + application/json and correct Phase selection; TC15 covers boundary-date correctness.
Query parameter permutations: TC01–TC08 and TC14 exercise combinations (both params, only subscriptionId, only requestedDate, none, invalid formats, extra params).
Input validation & error handling: TC03–TC08 and TC11 cover missing params, invalid formats, non-existent subscription, out-of-range dates and SQL-injection style inputs.
Authorization & security: TC09 tests unauthorized access (401); TC11 covers SQL injection handling and ensures internal errors are not exposed.
Service / dependency failures: TC10 covers upstream/unavailable dependency behavior (503).
Empty-data behavior: TC12 covers an empty database scenario (no subscriptions -> 404).
Performance & concurrency: TC13 addresses large dataset performance; TC16 checks concurrent request handling and response correctness under load.
Response semantics: Content-Type asserted for success in TC01 and status semantics (200 / 4xx / 5xx) are exercised across scenarios.
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover pagination headers/behavior — the suite does not verify pagination handling or page-size limits (if applicable).
Caching behavior: No tests for caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control, Last-Modified) or conditional GET behavior (If-None-Match -> 304).
Rate limiting / throttling: No tests for rate limits (429) or behavior under rapid-fire request bursts; TC16 is concurrency but not rate-limit validation.
Schema validation: No explicit validation against the Phase JSON schema (#/definitions/Phase) to ensure required fields, types and nested structures.
Error response structure & headers: Error scenarios do not consistently assert Content-Type or a stable error JSON schema for 4xx/5xx responses.
Authorization variants: 403 (forbidden / insufficient permissions) and other auth states (expired token, insufficient scope) are not covered — only 401 is tested.
Date/time variants & timezones: Missing tests for valid date-time variants (ISO8601 with timezone, date-time vs date-only), locale/format permutations, and edge cases (leap day, DST).
Deterministic default behavior when params omitted: TC02 allows either 200 or "default phase" — the expected behavior is ambiguous and not asserted deterministically.
Broader security coverage: Only SQL injection is covered; other vectors (XSS in returned payloads, header injection, malformed encoding) are not tested.
recommendations: Add Phase schema validation tests that assert response matches #/definitions/Phase (required properties, types, nested fields) for all success responses.
Add caching tests: verify presence/absence of ETag/Cache-Control headers and test conditional GETs (If-None-Match) to confirm correct 304 behavior when appropriate.
Add rate-limiting tests that simulate rapid bursts to verify 429 responses or configured throttling behavior and ensure graceful degradation.
Clarify and codify expected behavior when parameters are omitted (default vs error). Update TC02 to assert deterministic behavior that matches the API contract.
Add authorization matrix tests: 403 (valid token but insufficient permissions), expired token, and malformed token cases; assert consistent error payloads and headers.
Add date/time parsing tests for multiple valid formats (YYYY-MM-DD, ISO8601 with timezone, date-time boundaries) including leap-day and DST boundary checks.
Assert error response Content-Type and a consistent error JSON schema for all 4xx/5xx scenarios, and include schema checks for error fields (code/message/parameters).
If pagination is applicable for related endpoints, either mark pagination as N/A for this endpoint in the spec or add pagination tests (page/limit, out-of-range pages, performance with pages).
Extend security tests beyond SQLi (e.g., XSS in inputs/outputs, header injection, large-unicode payloads) and add malicious payload fuzzing for query parameters.
